WEBVTT

00:02.593 --> 00:04.761
(quietly): Hey, what took you so long?
Come on in.

00:04.762 --> 00:07.246
Hey. No, no. Why are we having
a secret meeting in an empty loft?

00:07.247 --> 00:09.265
Because I don't want Schmidt
to find us.

00:09.300 --> 00:11.167
- (shudders) It's creepy, right?
- I know, right?

00:11.168 --> 00:13.715
- Yeah, it is.
- This place gives me the willies, man.

00:13.716 --> 00:15.898
Do you know why they can't keep
a tenant in here?

00:15.919 --> 00:18.420
- Why?
- Because Mrs. Beverly died on the toilet.

00:18.421 --> 00:20.223
And to come here
on Halloween...?

00:20.256 --> 00:22.471
- Seems risky.
- What's risky?

00:22.472 --> 00:23.713
The ghost situation.

00:23.726 --> 00:26.037
I brought you guys in here
to talk about Schmidt.

00:26.038 --> 00:27.762
I'm really worried about him.

00:27.763 --> 00:29.498
He hasn't been to work
for three days.

00:29.532 --> 00:31.500
He just sits on the couch
eating cold cuts

00:31.534 --> 00:33.859
and yelling at the news
about how nothing matters.

00:33.860 --> 00:35.076
- It's a problem.
- Right.

00:35.077 --> 00:36.465
Be honest,
it's a real problem.

00:36.466 --> 00:38.114
He's just going through
a whole thing, you know?

00:38.115 --> 00:40.249
The Cece-Elizabeth breakup
has gotten to him.

00:40.250 --> 00:42.552
Right now
he is completely unhinged.

00:43.032 --> 00:45.237
- Y'all feel that?
- What is going on?

00:45.263 --> 00:47.453
Not saying there's a ghost, but I felt
a weird breeze go through my body,

00:47.454 --> 00:49.322
- that's all I'm saying.
- JESS: There's no ghost.

00:49.323 --> 00:51.490
Guys, I can't believe
I'm saying this, but...

00:51.530 --> 00:53.431
I miss the old Schmidt.

00:53.432 --> 00:55.484
I want him to be happy again.

00:55.485 --> 00:58.057
He's crumbling
before our very eyes.

00:58.061 --> 01:00.137
And I'm having a party tonight,

01:00.138 --> 01:02.206
and I just can't have him
lying on the couch,

01:02.207 --> 01:04.509
wiping his tears with deli meat.

01:04.510 --> 01:07.250
- I'll talk to him, okay?
- Thank you.

01:07.251 --> 01:10.919
People get weird with breakups.
Trust me, I got this.

01:10.920 --> 01:13.269
- (gruff voice): You got this.
- JESS: That was Winston.

01:13.270 --> 01:15.171
- Was that you or was that in here, dude?
- That was...

01:15.172 --> 01:16.632
Don't do that!

01:16.633 --> 01:17.833
(chuckles)

01:18.546 --> 01:21.414
Oh, come on, Obama.

01:21.449 --> 01:23.783
Tanks pull in, tanks pull out.

01:23.818 --> 01:27.354
Babies are born,
old people die.

01:27.388 --> 01:30.690
And yet the world keeps spinning
and spinning and spinning,

01:30.725 --> 01:32.425
and one day, it stops.

01:32.460 --> 01:34.094
And then what?

01:34.128 --> 01:37.230
You want... you want to talk
about... health care?

01:39.881 --> 01:41.114
That's mayo, buddy.

01:41.115 --> 01:43.737
(Nick, Jess and Winston groan)

01:43.771 --> 01:45.739
(whispers):
Yeah, I don't got this.

01:45.773 --> 01:48.141
(grunts)

01:48.176 --> 01:50.377
? Who's that girl?

01:50.411 --> 01:52.779
? <i>Who's that girl?</i> ?
? It's Jess.

01:52.804 --> 01:55.589
Season 3, Episode 6
"Keaton"

01:55.614 --> 01:58.614
Sync & corrections: Reef
www.addic7ed.com

01:58.753 --> 02:00.921
- ? Pumpkining...
- You're really good at that.

02:00.955 --> 02:03.590
Thanks, man. Yeah. What
are you carving there?

02:03.624 --> 02:05.625
- It's a pumpkin.
- Oh, look at that. That's beautiful.

02:05.660 --> 02:08.094
- My pumpkin!
- Pumpkin doesn't matter.

02:08.128 --> 02:11.131
Hey. I just wanted
to talk to you, um...

02:11.165 --> 02:14.968
- About my party tonight.
- You don't want me to come to the party?

02:15.002 --> 02:17.354
No, no, no, no, no, no.

02:17.355 --> 02:19.412
Jess, do you not want me
to come to your party?

02:19.424 --> 02:21.142
- No. I... No.
- Doesn't matter.

02:21.168 --> 02:24.511
I wouldn't go if I weren't
throwing it, you know?

02:24.512 --> 02:26.580
It's, like, more
of a business-networking...

02:26.581 --> 02:28.882
It's not a big deal at all.
I just won't come.

02:28.916 --> 02:31.429
I'll stay at home, and...
I'll just hang out in my costume.

02:31.430 --> 02:33.476
Oh, wait a minute.

02:33.521 --> 02:35.855
Your home is my home.

02:40.330 --> 02:41.928
See you at the party.
(door shuts)

02:41.963 --> 02:44.497
- What the hell?
- He's a total maniac.

02:44.532 --> 02:47.500
Well, you know what, Jess?
He doesn't get like this often.

02:47.535 --> 02:51.671
But when he does,
oh, there is an option.

02:51.706 --> 02:54.207
WINSTON: Nick, I think
it's time for Schmidt

02:54.242 --> 02:56.451
- to get a letter from an old friend.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

02:56.452 --> 02:58.134
- What old friend?
- Forget you heard anything.

02:58.135 --> 02:59.418
- What old friend?
- Nothing, J...

02:59.419 --> 03:00.783
- We need him, Nick.
- No, we don't.

03:00.808 --> 03:02.132
- We got to bring him back.
- Bring who back?

03:02.158 --> 03:04.611
- Winston, don't do this!
- Guys, does nobody listen to me?!

03:04.612 --> 03:05.931
- ...without him!
- Who is he?

03:06.187 --> 03:08.688
- Michael Keaton.
- You stupid...

03:08.689 --> 03:11.791
Michael Keaton, the actor?
The Batman?

03:11.792 --> 03:13.690
Nick, are you gonna tell her,
or should I?

03:13.691 --> 03:16.365
- I'm not telling her.
- Fine. I'll do it.

03:16.366 --> 03:18.934
- You will?
- When Schmidt was seven years old...

03:18.961 --> 03:22.443
(groans) You're a terrible storyteller.
I'll just do it myself, I guess.

03:24.705 --> 03:27.140
When Schmidt
was seven years old,

03:27.174 --> 03:29.142
his daddy divorced
his mommy...

03:29.176 --> 03:32.812
<i>And Schmidt was left
without the love of a father.</i>

03:32.847 --> 03:35.015
(crying)
<i>He didn't take it well.</i>

03:35.049 --> 03:37.910
<i>He began an endless cycle</i>
<i>of crying and chocolate.</i>

03:37.911 --> 03:42.255
<i>Mrs. Schmidt tried everything
to cheer him up, but nothing worked.</i>

03:42.290 --> 03:46.226
<i>Desperate, she looked to the stars.
Movie stars.</i>

03:46.260 --> 03:50.764
<i>Mrs. Schmidt wrote that little fat loser
a letter of support from the star</i>

03:50.798 --> 03:52.900
<i>of his favorite movie,
Batman.</i>

03:52.901 --> 03:56.536
<i>But not the confusing new one.
The good one, with Michael Keaton.</i>

03:57.972 --> 04:02.075
<i>And when Schmidt got his disgusting
chubby hands on Keaton's letter,</i>

04:02.076 --> 04:03.764
<i>his life changed forever.</i>

04:03.765 --> 04:04.970
Yes!

04:04.971 --> 04:06.905
<i>But the real trouble</i>
<i>was just beginning.</i>

04:06.906 --> 04:10.308
<i>You see, Schmidt wrote back.
And he kept writing back</i>

04:10.309 --> 04:14.196
<i>about any problem he faced:
bullies, schoolwork,</i>

04:14.197 --> 04:15.989
<i>public erections.</i>

04:16.023 --> 04:19.502
<i>And for every letter he sent,</i>
<i>Michael Keaton sent one back.</i>

04:19.517 --> 04:21.632
JESS:
<i>Was Winston's version shorter?</i>

04:21.632 --> 04:24.379
<i>NICK: Then one day, that tubby
goon went off to college.</i>

04:24.380 --> 04:25.598
Whoa.

04:25.633 --> 04:28.837
<i>So Mrs. Schmidt unloaded
the secret on her son's only friend,</i>

04:28.860 --> 04:31.271
<i>a man named me.
It was me.</i>

04:31.305 --> 04:33.106
<i>- JESS: Yeah, I got that.
- NICK: Really? People don't...</i>

04:33.140 --> 04:35.075
JESS:
<i>No, I got it.</i>

04:35.109 --> 04:38.395
<i>NICK: College proved tough for Schmidt,
and old patterns soon returned.</i>

04:38.396 --> 04:39.813
(crying)

04:39.847 --> 04:43.683
<i>It became impossible to study,</i>
<i>and I knew what I had to do.</i>

04:43.718 --> 04:44.984
<i>And again...</i>

04:45.019 --> 04:46.786
<i>- New message.
- ...It worked.</i>

04:46.821 --> 04:50.612
<i>With Keaton in his corner, he pulled
himself away from that bag of turkey</i>

04:50.613 --> 04:52.392
<i>- ...and became a man.</i>
- One...

04:52.426 --> 04:55.829
<i>He lost five pounds,
gained confidence with women...</i>

04:57.431 --> 04:59.999
<i>...and he saw the hit movie
Multiplicity...</i>

05:00.034 --> 05:02.321
- 25 times.
- Oh, my God.

05:02.322 --> 05:04.223
You've been cat fishing Schmidt.

05:04.224 --> 05:06.306
Do you think we could use
this whole Michael Keaton thing

05:06.307 --> 05:08.141
- ...to turn Schmidt around?
- Absolutely.

05:08.142 --> 05:09.852
- Great!
- But I won't do it.

05:09.878 --> 05:12.145
- Why not?
- Because I put it to bed, okay?

05:12.179 --> 05:14.848
It's over. He'll do
anything Keaton says.

05:14.882 --> 05:16.480
The letters are
too powerful.

05:16.481 --> 05:18.481
I'm lying to my best friend.

05:18.519 --> 05:21.675
And I also feel like I'm betraying
the real Keaton, who I really love.

05:21.676 --> 05:24.112
Well, then why did you tell me
that whole story, Nick?

05:24.113 --> 05:26.591
Because it's a great story,
and I'm a teller of stories.

05:26.592 --> 05:28.762
But I won't do it. Sorry.

05:28.796 --> 05:30.597
You think you tell that story
better than me?

05:30.631 --> 05:32.432
Look, you leave out
way too many details, man.

05:32.433 --> 05:34.530
You don't just say
he was chewing a candy bar.

05:34.531 --> 05:37.289
You say he was chewing
on a <i>nougat-y</i> candy bar.

05:37.290 --> 05:40.523
NICK: That's not the kind of writer I am.
I don't say words like "nougat-y."

05:40.524 --> 05:42.847
I'm simple.
I'm like Hemingway.

